<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, To the handful of people around the world who specialize in the field of 
photomicrography, small is truly beautiful. Using such tools as electron 
microscopes, these people see a world hidden from the human eye. Polaroid Corp. 
sponsors an annual contest and this year received more than 600 entries of 
molecular-scale photographs. Two of the winners are shown here. One, in the 
photo at left, shows red blood cells clinging to the tip of a hypodermic 
needle. The other shows two hair cells on the surface of a pinto bean leaf that 
became entangled as they developed. Polaroid Corp. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
