<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONFIRMATION HEARINGS FOR JUDGE SOUTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was distressed to find that you buried the story about women's and civil 
rights groups' opposition to Judge Souter. 
</P>
<P>
I thought surely that the impassioned and well-stated fears from such people as 
Faye Wattleton of Planned Parenthood and those from other prominent civil 
rights groups would merit front-page news coverage. Instead, it is buried 
inside ("Reject Souter, Backers of Abortion Rights Say," Part A, Sept. 19). 
</P>
<P>
To top it off, I read an uninspired "endorsement" of him (editorial, "The Price 
of Independence") with a plea to not see him as a "single-issue" person. Would 
you feel the same if the issue were the First Amendment? 
</P>
<P>
VALERIE DUFRESNE 
</P>
<P>
Corona 
</P>
</TEXT>
