<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPAIN'S MARTINEZ WINS PARIS OPEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Conchita Martinez of Spain won the Paris women's open Sunday, defeating 
Patricia Tarabini of Argentina, 7-5, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
"It was a very hard final for me because Tarabini has a way to play which is 
very different from other players," Martinez said. 
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Spaniard, who reached the French Open quarterfinals in 1988 and 
the finals of the European Open in 1989, has been less successful recently. 
</P>
<P>
"My victory today brought me back confidence in myself and it feels really 
great to win," said the tournament's top-seeded player. 
</P>
