<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Groundlings Grounded?The long-running Groundlings improvisational comedy troupe 
may be forced to shut down if $30,000 cannot be raised by the end of the year 
to cover its financial difficulties. In the last 16 years, the Melrose Avenue 
group has served as a launching pad for such stars as Pee-wee Herman, Cassandra 
(Elvira) Peterson, Pat Morita and Jon Lovitz. 
</P>
<P>
But with expenses exceeding income, the group's executive director, Andrea 
Ladik, announced they are looking for a financial "miracle." Through 
advertisements and personal appeals, the Groundlings are asking for donations 
from the theater-going public. An honor roll is being installed in the theater 
lobby to salute donors, and a one-night gala event, "The Best of the 
Groundlings," will be held this fall. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
