<P>
MORNING REPORT: OPERA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Designing Sendak: Original paintings by artist Maurice Sendak created for the 
L.A. Music Center Opera's new production of Mozart's "Idomeneo" will go on 
exhibit Tuesday at Every Picture Tells a Story . . . , the Los Angeles gallery 
devoted to original art from children's literature. Sendak, who has created and 
illustrated more than 30 books, including "Higglety Pigglety Pop," "In the 
Night Kitchen" and "Where the Wild Things Are," said he has had a lifelong 
ambition to design the Mozart opera, an epic tale of the Trojan War. 
</P>
<P>
The opera will also premiere Tuesday at the Dorothy Chandler Pavilion. Sendak 
has created sets for other operas, including works based on "Where the Wild 
Things Are" and "Higglety Pigglety Pop," which also have been presented by the 
Music Center Opera. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
