<P>
Cates Gets the Dean's Cap: Producer-director Gilbert Cates has been named dean 
of UCLA's School of Theater, Film and Television. 
</P>
<P>
Cates will serve the school as its chief administrator and as a professor with 
joint appointments in the Theater/Film and Television departments. He is 
expected to assume his new post no later than April 1 of next year. Cates, who 
was nominated for an Emmy for producing this year's Academy Awards, was 
appointed last week by Academy of Motion Pictures Arts and Sciences President 
Karl Malden to helm next year's ceremony. GREG BRAXTON 
