<TYPE>
<P>
Wild Art 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092490-0063 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 282202 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 24, 1990, Monday, San Diego County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 4 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
133 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEOG COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man, suffering from multiple stab wounds, stumbled into the 
lobby of a downtown hotel Sunday evening, collapsed on the floor and died, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
The man entered the Serra Francis Hometel at 943 10th Avenue at 5:25 p.m. and 
died at the scene, said a spokesman for the San Diego Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
Paramedics responded, but the man was dead by the time they arrived, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Police believe the stabbing occurred at 917 10th Ave. and that the man fled the 
scene to seek help at the hotel, the spokesman said. Witnesses told police that 
a fight had broken out at that address and that the suspect fled shortly before 
the victim reached the hotel, the spokesman added. 
</P>
<P>
A suspect, Junius Derouen, 25, was later arrested and booked into County Jail 
on suspicion of murder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
