<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIMES FAXES NEWS TO TROOPS IN GULF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Times is sending a daily news digest to troops in the Persian 
Gulf, using facsimile transmission to deliver the newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
The eight-page digest includes news from the gulf, the world, the nation and 
California, as well as comics and sports. 
</P>
<P>
The Times is sending the news digest to the military command in Riyadh, which, 
in turn, is sending it to troop units from all the services equipped with fax 
receivers. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, The Times is working with Marine units at Camp Pendleton to 
deliver copies of the full newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. military officials and reservists have said that the troops want regular 
news service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES TIMES; UNITED STATES -- ARMED FORCES -- PERSIAN GULF; MORALE; 
NEWSPAPERS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
