<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAUDI ARABIA CANCELS NATIONAL DAY FESTIVITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RIYADH, Saudi Arabia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government canceled all official celebrations of the kingdom's National Day 
holiday Sunday as a gesture of solidarity with the Kuwaiti people. 
</P>
<P>
The official Saudi Press Agency said the royal court had informed Saudi 
embassies worldwide to refrain from official celebrations because of the 
suffering endured by the Kuwaiti people since the Aug. 2 Iraqi invasion. 
</P>
<P>
National Day, which marks the 1932 consolidation of power by King Adbulaziz ibn 
Saud, is traditionally celebrated with parades and festivals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
