<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE ARREST MAN IN HIT-AND-RUN DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Oxnard man was killed by a hit-and-run driver while walking across Saviers 
Road early Sunday, an Oxnard police spokesman said. A witness's tip led to the 
arrest of a suspect, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jesus Hernandez, 28, suffered multiple injuries and was pronounced dead at St. 
John's Regional Medical Center after the 12:30 a.m. accident, Deputy Coroner 
Jim Wingate said. 
</P>
<P>
Hernandez was crossing Saviers Road near Date Street in an area where there is 
no crosswalk and was struck by a pickup truck, Sgt. Ken Nishihara said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver sped away, Nishihara said, but a witness followed the pickup for a 
short while before stopping at a pay phone to call police. 
</P>
<P>
Police immediately broadcast a description of the vehicle, and minutes later a 
California Highway Patrol officer stopped Jose Antonio Mejia in his pickup on 
the Ventura Freeway at Las Posas Road in Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect put up no resistance, Nishihara said. 
</P>
<P>
Mejia, 22, of Oxnard was arrested on suspicion of vehicular manslaughter and 
felony hit-and-run and was released on $10,000 bail. CHRISTOPHER PUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
