<P>
4 DIE IN SAN LUIS OBISPO CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN LUIS OBISPO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A private jet crashed today as the pilot attempted to land in heavy morning fog 
at the municipal airport, killing at least four of the five people reported 
aboard, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The twin-engine Cessna Citation, flying out of Van Nuys Airport, went down at 
7:03 a.m. in a field about three miles northwest of the San Luis Obispo 
Airport, Federal Aviation Administration spokesman Fred O'Donnell said. 
</P>
