<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
CITY PROCLAIMS 'FREE KUWAIT DAY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles proclaimed today "Free Kuwait Day" in a show of solidarity with 
Kuwaiti citizens in the United States who oppose Iraq's invasion and occupation 
of their nation. 
</P>
<P>
Donning red-and-white T-shirts bearing the message "Free Kuwait," about two 
dozen Kuwaitis and local supporters joined in a ceremony on the steps of City 
Hall to receive a proclamation signed by Mayor Tom Bradley and members of the 
City Council. 
</P>
<P>
"This is to send the message out that we are opposed to Iraq's actions and that 
we sympathize with the cause of the Kuwaitis here," Councilman Michael Woo 
said. "No people should be subject to takeover by another." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
