<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANDIDATE CALLS FOR VIGILANTE CORPS TO BATTLE N.Y. CRIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ALBANY, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Maverick GOP gubernatorial candidate Pierre Rinfret today called for armed 
vigilantes to battle crime in New York City. 
</P>
<P>
"What I really want is a vigilante system with people carrying guns, unknown to 
anybody, so anybody who comes along and mugs somebody may have, standing next 
to him, a man who's been authorized," Rinfret said. 
</P>
<P>
Aides later said the Manhattan-based economist envisioned a volunteer corps of 
up to 100,000 police-trained vigilantes. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Gov. Mario M. Cuomo, Rinfret's opponent, dismissed the proposal 
as dangerous. 
</P>
</TEXT>
