<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
SHELTON SETS AIR RACE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
RENO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lyle Shelton set a speed record Sunday to win his third consecutive Unlimited 
Gold championship at the National Air Races. 
</P>
<P>
Shelton, 57, of Granada Hills set a race record of 468.6 m.p.h., breaking his 
own 1988 record by more than 10 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
Shelton, in his modified Grumman Bearcat, beat second-place finisher Skip Holm 
of Woodland Hills to win the $50,000 first prize. 
</P>
