<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
ATLANTA STAGES OLYMPIC PARADE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Olympic fever was rampant in the Georgia capital today as Atlanta staged its 
first ticker-tape parade to celebrate its designation as host of the 1996 
Summer Games. 
</P>
<P>
Thousands of spectators lined the parade route, pelting Mayor Maynard Jackson 
and other dignitaries with confetti and streamers as they rode by. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm the guy who's got to clean this stuff up," Jackson laughed as he and his 
wife, Valerie, tried to brush the paper from their hair. 
</P>
<P>
Police estimated that 50,000 people had gathered for the parade by 11:30 a.m. 
EDT. Atlanta schools excused children from class to attend, with parental 
approval. 
</P>
</TEXT>
