<P>
ITALIANS LAUD TRUDEAU, VIDAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FORTE DEI MARMI, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American cartoonist Garry Trudeau and author Gore Vidal were honored for 
political satire and literature. 
</P>
<P>
"Doonesbury" comic strip creator Trudeau was awarded Italy's Forte dei Marmi 
Prize for satire. Vidal, best known for his historical novels "Burr" and 
"Lincoln," received the literary award for his book "Hollywood." 
</P>
<P>
The two received their awards Saturday in this town near Lucca in Tuscany. 
</P>
</TEXT>
