</P>
<P>
CHILE LIFTS BAN ON 'FIDDLER' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTIAGO, Chile 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government today lifted a 16-year-old ban on the movie "Fiddler on the 
Roof," condemned by the former military regime for its alleged Marxist content. 
</P>
<P>
The new civilian government said its decree was necessary "because the nation 
has started a time of real implementation of the principles of democracy and 
freedom." 
</P>
</TEXT>
